column6: The 1956 "Wu experiment" on the beta-decay of Cobalt-60 was conducted by Chinese-American physicist Chien-Shiung Wu and changed the way physicists see the universe, though Wu was excluded from the 1957 Nobel prize recognising the discovery. What did her experiment demonstrate?
column7: Parity non-conservation/violation (that it is possible to distinguish the universe from its mirror image).

column6: Susan Brown is believed to have been the first female mathematics professor in the UK. She published many papers on triple-deck theory and boundary layers. What field of math did she work in?
In 1925, who became the first African-American mathematician to be awarded a PhD? He graduated from Cornell.

column7: ARM (Advanced RISC Machine, originally Acorn RISC Machine)

column6: "The Glass Universe: How the Ladies of the Harvard Observatory Took the Measure of the Stars" was written by which best-selling science author?
Who penned "A Brief History of Everyone Who Ever Lived: The Stories in Our Genes"?
Shirakawa shared the 2000 Nobel Prize in Chemistry with physicist Alan Jay Heeger and chemist Alan Graham MacDiarmid for discovering and developing polymers with what property?
Who is known for the discovery of C−H···O hydrogen bonds? She later worked with Kathleen Lonsdale on the characterisation and prevention of urinary calculi.
The Boy Who Harnessed the Wind' is a 2019 British drama film written, directed by and starring which Black British actor?  He also starred in 12 years a slave.

How many Nobel prizes have been awarded to black people in physics, chemistry, and physiology or medicine?

Kimberlé Williams Crenshaw coined what term that is now associated with a branch of feminism which identifies how different aspects of social and political discrimination overlap with gender?

In linguistics, what two word phrase is given to: the belief or impression that a word or language usage is of recent origin when it is long-established? The term was coined by Arnold Zwicky.

Who am I? From 1974-92 I directed the Medical Research Council’s Mammalian development unit in London. I mainly worked in embryology and using mice. In 1991 I became the Royal society’s foreign secretary.

column7: For every symmetry there is a corresponding conservation law.

column7: Location: University of Bologna - Era: 1732 till 1776
